<p>Here we will limit ourselves to data representation.</p>
<h3>Common challenges with data representation</h3>
<ul>
<li><p>Polysemy &#40;homograph&#41;: A single term refers to multiple concepts</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Mercury could refer to a mythical being, a planet, a metal, an automobile</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>Synonymy: Multiple terms refer to the same concept  â€“ AMI&#61;Acute Myocardial Infarctus&#61;Infarctus of the myocardium&#61;Heart attack</p>
<ul>
<li><p>salinity&#61;saltiness</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>Imprecision: Lack of specificities   â€“ e.g., infarctus?</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>These all lead to ambiguity.</p>
<h3>Standards Solution</h3>
<p>The foundational idea is referred to as the tripartite &quot;Concept Based Representation&quot;</p>
<p><img src="https://github.com/chapmanbe/raw-stuff/blob/main/Standards/concept_based_representation.png?raw&#61;true" alt="Concept based representation" /></p>
<h3>A Few Principles of Successful Standards</h3>
<ol>
<li><p>Formal definition</p>
<ul>
<li><p>The standard provides a formal definition of the concept.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>Terminology and synonyms</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Provides the preferred term for the concept as well as any synonyms</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>Concept orientation</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Each concept has one unambiguous, non-redundant meaning</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>Concept permanence</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Old concepts cannot be deleted</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>Non-semantic identifiers</p>
<ul>
<li><p>The ID of a concept is not a name, it is not a code that will run out of room, and it is not a place in a hierarchy.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><p>Poly-hierarchy</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Allow for multiple parent concepts </p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<h3>Example: SNOMED-CT Representation of Lisinopril</h3>
<ul>
<li><p>Formal definition: SNOMED-CT does not define what lisinopril is</p>
</li>
<li><p>Terminology and synonyms: preferred term is &quot;lisinopril&quot;</p>
</li>
<li><p>ID: 386873009 &#40;this is non semantic&#41;</p>
</li>
<li><p>Poly-hierarchy</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><img src="https://github.com/chapmanbe/raw-stuff/blob/main/Standards/snomed_lisinopril_viz.png?raw&#61;true" alt="lisinopril SNOMED Visualization" /></p>
