<p><img src="https://github.com/chapmanbe/raw-stuff/blob/main/Standards/lisinopril_aumed1.png?raw&#61;true" alt="lisinopril AU" /></p>
<h4>Why are there so many standards?</h4>
<p>Recall &quot;Standards are like toothbrushes, everyone agrees that theyâ€™re a good idea but nobody wants to use anyone elseâ€™s.&quot; </p>
<p>But also standards are developed for a particular context and are abstractions for that context. Recalling Picasso&#39;s bulls, the <em>essence</em> of lisinopril differs, depending on the context.</p>
